rComments: J'aimais ce cours ainsi que le prof. Les cours étaient pleins d'exemples concrets. J'aimais l'alternance avec des invités. Le prof était jovial et disponible à répondre aux sollicitations des étudiants. Je le recommande.
Very inspirational professor. I learnt about different cultural perspectives on traditional treatment. He was kind and joyful towards every student.

I learnt a lot thanks to this Professor. He was very kind and sweet to every student. He was not particularly knowlegeable about medical anthropology, but he used to convey different methods to enable us understand the course: videos, visiting professors, presentations. I particularly loved the open discussion part.

He was an open minded and kind person. He informed us from start that he was not a specialist of medical anthropology and was willing to help since there was a lack of teachers. I am happy that he tried all his best and invited a couple of specialists to cover area he didnt master enough . I will definitely recommend him
Best professor ever. Relaxed, good minded person. Iike his personality and his dynamism. Besides, I liked the fact that he offered us to debate and dicuss about eveyreading.

I loved the way this course was organized: students' presentations, Professor's interventions and above all reputable visiting Professors. This made the course very active with a new area to explore every day.
This Professor had clear reading criteria. He was always available to help. As a PhD student, I didn't expect him to master everything but I am satisfied with his work.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: He was an inspirational and motivational speaker. I liked the way he was fluent in French. This strengthened my French skills too. I am not sure if he will read my comments, but I am proud of him.

Professor Richard is definitely one of the best teachers I have ever had. Energetic, patient and intelligent, he really knows how to Care for his students. He always pushed me to think critically about medicine.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: I enjoyed every day I had a lecture with this Professor. Always joyful and helpful, he has enabled me to understand the limits of biology and the need to consider traditional medicine. Anyone who is bored by modern medicine should consider taking this course. I will definitely recommend this professor in the future.

Mr. Richard Atimniraye was a very good Professor. I loved the fact that he always he related the course to real life situations. We also had the chance of having some visiting professors who brought in more insights to the course.

This teacher was very competent and skilled. Every day spent in the the class was full of new discoveries in the deep and interesting domain of medical anthropology. I would highly recommend him for the next teachings.

Every second spent in this class was painful. Honestly never had a worse prof at UOttawa or anywhere else. Can't even compare. He's nice enough though. No grading criterion and seems to need to be taught the class rather than be teaching it.

my time spent in this class can be resumed in one word: awful. The worst class I have ever taken in my whole academic career. Barely teaches. He is not ill-intentioned but some people just should not be allowed to teach.

Just one piece of advice if you have this prof : RUN. Honestly, I considered going into medical anthropology and never thought I could hate it - I was clearly wrong. Barely teaches. Also, the grading criterion and expectations are so unclear for the assignments, even he seems unsure of them.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']
